%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.types import *

def look (r):
    result = []
    result.append ("{}".format (r))
    return result
        
class CTDExposureEvents(object):
    def __init__(self, path):
        self.path = path
        self.rdd = self.load ()
        self.rdd.toDF().registerTempTable ('ctd_exposure_events')

    def load (self, sample_size=1.0):
        return sqlContext.read.                                     \
            format('com.databricks.spark.csv').                     \
            options(comment='#').                                   \
            options(delimiter=",").                                 \
            options(header='true').                                 \
            load(self.path).rdd.                                   \
            sample (False, sample_size, 1234)

    def get_events (self, stressor_agent_id=None):
        return self.rdd.filter (lambda r : r.stressoragentid == stressor_agent_id)

ctd_expo_data = '/projects/stars/translator/var/ctd/CTD_exposure_events.csv'
ctd_exposure_events = CTDExposureEvents (ctd_expo_data)

pm25_agent_id = 'D052638'
pm25_events = ctd_exposure_events.get_events (stressor_agent_id=pm25_agent_id)
print (pm25_events.take (10))

asthma_mesh_id = 'D001249'
